Configuration File - Defines the parameters to be used during a codedeploy deployment

it is by far mostly written in yaml 

in case of the lambdas and ec2 it can be written in yaml json

PARTS OF THE FILE:


1) VERSION 


2) OS - THE OS DEPLOYING TO 

3) FILES - THE LOCATION OF ANY APPLICATION FILES THAT NEED TO BE COPIED AND WHERE THEY SHOULD BE COPIED TO 

HOOKS - Scripts which need to run at set points in the deployment lifecycle. Hooks have a very specific run order.
